01:19:48,847 --> 01:19:50,576
See you tomorrow.

783
01:19:58,590 --> 01:20:00,490
Franz would have given a lot...

784
01:20:00,592 --> 01:20:04,892
His gold watch, his American books,
his two hands, he didn't know exactly...

785
01:20:04,997 --> 01:20:07,591
But he would have given a lot
to console Odile.

786
01:20:07,833 --> 01:20:09,824
One only had to look at her

787
01:20:10,002 --> 01:20:12,937
to realize the world
was crumbling around her.

788
01:21:03,021 --> 01:21:05,387
This is crazy. We'll be spotted.

789
01:21:05,691 --> 01:21:07,716
We'll say we're TV people.

790
01:21:07,826 --> 01:21:09,794
TV is the open sesame.

791
01:21:22,174 --> 01:21:23,539
So, got the key?

792
01:21:23,642 --> 01:21:26,236
- It's not 5:00 yet.
- We're in a hurry.

793
01:21:26,412 --> 01:21:28,903
Anyway, it's no good now.

794
01:21:29,114 --> 01:21:31,639
You left traces with the ladder.

795
01:21:32,050 --> 01:21:35,508
When I came home,
all the locks were changed.

796
01:21:35,721 --> 01:21:39,054
Mr. Stolz's room,
the windows, the doors.

797
01:21:39,792 --> 01:21:41,692
Did she say anything?

798
01:21:43,095 --> 01:21:45,256
She doesn't suspect me yet.

799
01:21:45,497 --> 01:21:47,727
Get out of here, please.

800
01:21:56,475 --> 01:21:58,102
Help!

801
01:21:58,710 --> 01:22:00,905
Get out!
Odile, tell them to leave.

802
01:22:01,113 --> 01:22:02,876
I don't know what to do.

803
01:22:03,382 --> 01:22:05,543
Please don't hurt her.

804
01:22:05,851 --> 01:22:08,046
The key to Mr. Stolz's room.

805
01:22:08,253 --> 01:22:12,417
You're wasting your time.
He has nothing of value.

806
01:22:12,658 --> 01:22:14,683
We want to see for ourselves.

807
01:22:16,962 --> 01:22:18,793
Okay. The key.

808
01:22:20,098 --> 01:22:23,363
You can't scare me. It's not loaded.

809
01:22:35,113 --> 01:22:36,808
Tie her up.

810
01:22:37,015 --> 01:22:39,506
- With what?
- Where's your hair ribbon?

811
01:22:39,618 --> 01:22:40,915
No, Franz, no!

812
01:22:41,019 --> 01:22:43,419
I'm warning you, I mean business.

813
01:22:43,989 --> 01:22:45,581
Lie facedown.

814
01:22:47,359 --> 01:22:48,883
Tie her arms in back.

815
01:22:48,994 --> 01:22:50,791
You know these men?

816
01:22:51,964 --> 01:22:53,864
I've never seen them before.

817
01:22:54,066 --> 01:22:55,863
Any cotton in the bathroom?

818
01:22:55,968 --> 01:22:57,731
I don't know.

819
01:22:57,836 --> 01:22:59,235
Go look.

820
01:22:59,338 --> 01:23:02,068
Not in my mouth. I won't scream.

821
01:23:02,241 --> 01:23:05,267
Please. I promise I won't make trouble.

822
01:23:05,444 --> 01:23:07,275
Shut the hell up, ma'am.

823
01:23:10,315 --> 01:23:13,648
Please forgive me, Madame Victoria.
Forgive me.

824
01:23:15,587 --> 01:23:17,987
I trusted you and you do this to me.

825
01:23:19,825 --> 01:23:21,656
Open the closet.

826
01:23:21,760 --> 01:23:23,318
Open your mouth.

827
01:23:28,967 --> 01:23:32,960
We'll hide her here.
Old man Stolz won't find her so fast.

828
01:23:33,238 --> 01:23:35,502
Say she went out to see someone.

829
01:23:35,908 --> 01:23:38,138
Clear out first chance you get.

830
01:23:48,120 --> 01:23:50,111
Stay here. I'm going up.

831
01:23:55,060 --> 01:23:57,551
You're completely nuts!

832
01:24:02,634 --> 01:24:04,693
Why don't you love me?

833
01:24:05,070 --> 01:24:06,833
This is hardly the time.

834
01:24:13,612 --> 01:24:16,103
I want to hold you in my arms.

835
01:24:17,983 --> 01:24:20,008
What is it now?

836
01:24:36,935 --> 01:24:38,664
The money's gone.

837
01:24:41,640 --> 01:24:43,540
This all? Where's the money?

838
01:24:43,742 --> 01:24:46,176
How should I know? I don't know.

839
01:24:46,712 --> 01:24:48,543
Let's search the place.

840
01:25:24,883 --> 01:25:26,510
This was in the garage.

841
01:25:26,618 --> 01:25:29,644
And this in the tub,
and this in Odile's room.

842
01:25:29,755 --> 01:25:31,518
Where'd she go?

843
01:25:33,191 --> 01:25:36,126
Check the fridge.
It's a housewife's safe.

844
01:25:38,697 --> 01:25:40,358
Where's the rest of it?

845
01:25:43,301 --> 01:25:44,859
I don't know.

846
01:25:45,037 --> 01:25:46,971
You were right. I found this.

847
01:25:48,306 --> 01:25:50,240
Was the pile this big?

848
01:25:50,642 --> 01:25:53,008
- No, bigger.
- This big?

849
01:25:55,147 --> 01:25:56,739
Yes, like that.

850
01:25:57,482 --> 01:25:59,347
That's enough. Let's go.

851
01:25:59,985 --> 01:26:01,680
We'll make that goose talk.

852
01:26:01,920 --> 01:26:05,549
Don't hurt her.
She'll have to tell us the truth.

853
01:26:06,124 --> 01:26:08,854
Just threaten her.
- Okay.

854
01:26:13,031 --> 01:26:16,262
Tell us where the money is
or we'll torch the house.

855
01:26:21,973 --> 01:26:23,531
She fainted.

856
01:26:30,716 --> 01:26:32,343
She's not breathing.

857
01:26:33,852 --> 01:26:36,446
She's dead.
- You killed her!

858
01:26:39,257 --> 01:26:41,122
We better beat it.

859
01:26:44,429 --> 01:26:46,590
Odile, darling! Let's go.

860
01:27:23,935 --> 01:27:26,096
Arthur suddenly wanted to go back.

861
01:27:26,271 --> 01:27:28,831
To make sure,
he said in an odd voice,

862
01:27:28,940 --> 01:27:32,171
that the lady was really dead,
just to avoid any problems.

863
01:27:32,277 --> 01:27:34,643
They'd meet at the Tout Va Bien,

864
01:27:34,846 --> 01:27:37,007
a café just off the highway.

865
01:27:54,866 --> 01:27:57,562
Suddenly, Franz saw the uncle's car.

866
01:27:57,936 --> 01:28:00,496
Like the hero of a legendary romance,

867
01:28:00,872 --> 01:28:03,306
he suddenly had a dark foreboding.

868
01:28:03,508 --> 01:28:05,567
Despite Odile's pleadings,

869
01:28:05,677 --> 01:28:10,080
he did a U-turn and the car
obediently retraced its route.

870
01:29:15,380 --> 01:29:16,847
Hey, asshole!

871
01:30:03,561 --> 01:30:07,292
Arthur's dying thought
was of Odile's face.

872
01:30:07,532 --> 01:30:10,262
As a dark fog descended on him,

873
01:30:10,368 --> 01:30:13,132
he saw that fabled bird
of Indian legend,

874
01:30:13,338 --> 01:30:17,172
which is born without feet,
and thus can never alight.

875
01:30:17,575 --> 01:30:20,271
It sleeps in the high winds,

876
01:30:20,378 --> 01:30:22,744
and is only visible when it dies.

877
01:30:23,014 --> 01:30:24,948
When its transparent wings,

878
01:30:25,050 --> 01:30:27,018
longer than an eagle's, fold in,

879
01:30:27,118 --> 01:30:28,949
it fits in the palm of your hand.

880
01:31:47,565 --> 01:31:50,329
- You want to get us killed?
- Absolutely.

881
01:31:50,869 --> 01:31:52,393
What's got into you?

882
01:31:52,504 --> 01:31:54,062
I'm disgusted with life.

883
01:31:55,106 --> 01:31:57,097
We didn't make out so bad.

884
01:31:57,509 --> 01:31:59,602
Nothing to get dramatic about.

885
01:32:00,111 --> 01:32:01,874
But I feel terrible.

886
01:32:04,949 --> 01:32:06,610
So do I.

887
01:32:08,186 --> 01:32:10,416
Why don't you close the hood?

888
01:32:10,889 --> 01:32:13,517
It doesn't close.

889
01:32:14,893 --> 01:32:17,521
Think Mr. Stolz will call the police?

890
01:32:18,063 --> 01:32:21,191
Not likely. It's money
he stole from the government.

891
01:32:22,267 --> 01:32:25,168
Isn't it?
- Yes, it is.

892
01:32:30,942 --> 01:32:34,901
Isn't it strange how people
never form a whole?

893
01:32:35,480 --> 01:32:37,072
In what way?

894
01:32:39,350 --> 01:32:41,648
They never come together.

895
01:32:42,387 --> 01:32:44,514
They remain separate.

896
01:32:45,323 --> 01:32:47,723
Each goes his own way,

897
01:32:48,726 --> 01:32:51,126
distrustful and tragic.

898
01:32:52,864 --> 01:32:55,856
Even when they're together,
in big buildings,

899
01:32:56,568 --> 01:32:58,399
or in the street.

900
01:32:59,938 --> 01:33:01,872
Don't feel like talking?

901
01:33:07,145 --> 01:33:10,205
When I said I wanted
to hold you back there,

902
01:33:11,015 --> 01:33:12,812
were you listening?

903
01:33:12,917 --> 01:33:15,112
Yes, I was.

904
01:33:16,888 --> 01:33:18,947
But you're still sad?

905
01:33:21,326 --> 01:33:23,920
I'm not as sad as all that.

906
01:33:24,596 --> 01:33:26,928
Then what are you?

907
01:33:27,632 --> 01:33:30,533
I'm worn out from sorrow and fatigue.

908
01:33:32,470 --> 01:33:34,233
What will you do then?

909
01:33:34,339 --> 01:33:35,806
And you?

910
01:33:36,841 --> 01:33:39,833
I can't decide between the north

911
01:33:40,478 --> 01:33:42,309
and the south.

912
01:33:43,781 --> 01:33:45,544
You decide.

913
01:33:45,717 --> 01:33:48,880
I... me... myself... us.

914
01:33:49,721 --> 01:33:52,781
I... you... yourself... you.

915
01:33:53,124 --> 01:33:56,685
His... their... your... our...

916
01:33:57,428 --> 01:33:58,986
their...

917
01:34:00,365 --> 01:34:02,230
South.

918
01:34:11,309 --> 01:34:14,836
Three days later,
Odile and Franz saw the sea.

919
01:34:15,213 --> 01:34:17,613
It looked like a theater,

920
01:34:17,715 --> 01:34:20,013
with the horizon as its stage,

921
01:34:20,185 --> 01:34:22,517
and beyond it nothing but sky.

922
01:34:22,754 --> 01:34:25,689
Before the gently spreading waves
of this harmony,

923
01:34:25,957 --> 01:34:29,586
Franz and Odile saw
neither limits nor contradictions.

924
01:34:31,129 --> 01:34:32,790
Are there lions in Brazil?

925
01:34:32,897 --> 01:34:35,764
As well as croc... Odiles.

926
01:34:36,134 --> 01:34:37,795
Thinking of me?

927
01:34:37,936 --> 01:34:39,665
Obviously.

928
01:34:39,771 --> 01:34:41,295
In what way?

929
01:34:41,906 --> 01:34:44,033
The way you think about me.

930
01:34:44,609 --> 01:34:46,406
When guys think of girls,

931
01:34:46,511 --> 01:34:49,742
they think about their eyes,
legs and breasts.

932
01:34:50,648 --> 01:34:53,412
Girls think of guys
in exactly the same way.

933
01:34:53,885 --> 01:34:55,648
So we're in love?

934
01:34:55,887 --> 01:34:57,718
We'll see soon enough.

935
01:35:03,728 --> 01:35:06,288
Put your hand around the ball.

936
01:35:07,699 --> 01:35:10,293
The liquid should flow across...

937
01:35:10,602 --> 01:35:12,502
if you love me.

938
01:35:15,873 --> 01:35:19,001
My story ends here,
like in a pulp novel,

939
01:35:19,110 --> 01:35:21,704
at that superb moment
when nothing weakens,

940
01:35:21,946 --> 01:35:24,176
nothing wears away, nothing wanes.

941
01:35:24,582 --> 01:35:26,743
An upcoming film will reveal,

942
01:35:26,851 --> 01:35:29,115
in CinemaScope and Technicolor,

943
01:35:29,354 --> 01:35:32,084
the tropical adventures
of Odile and Franz.

